    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/enNdg.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 21994,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 53897,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/53897/thorbj%c3%b8rn-ravn-andersen",
                "reputation": 75391,
                "display_name": "Thorbj&#248;rn Ravn Andersen",
                "accept_rate": 56
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292415427,
            "creation_date": 1292415427,
            "body": "<p>Setting a variable to null just removes a reference to the object.  it does not change the actual object.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you need to clean up, you most likely need to do actions to the object referenced by your variable instead.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449762,
            "question_id": 4449721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/42923efa8294fa67466d94418b6c3f12?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 85265,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 237838,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/237838/andrew-barber",
                "reputation": 40321,
                "display_name": "Andrew Barber",
                "accept_rate": 86
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292415133,
            "creation_date": 1292415133,
            "body": "<p>Assigning an object reference the value <code>null<\/code> does not 'empty the data'; it merely sets that variable reference to <code>null<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449729,
            "question_id": 4449721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/868514b645114d05d1e57d671a116b3a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 3690,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5353,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5353/sylvain-defresne",
                "reputation": 45173,
                "display_name": "Sylvain Defresne"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292415222,
            "creation_date": 1292415222,
            "body": "<p>It probably wants you to use the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Null_Object_pattern\" rel=\"nofollow\">Null Object pattern<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449741,
            "question_id": 4449721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/78b16260fc79e38d1d9f2de2ddb22e7a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 8208109,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6177195,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6177195/alexsander-caproni",
                "reputation": 117,
                "display_name": "Alexsander Caproni",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1540910353,
            "creation_date": 1540910353,
            "body": "<p>Just set your variable to <code>final<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>For instance, if there is the following code, SONAR will report as a code smell:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private Object obj = null;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>However, if you just add final, it can be resolved.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private final Object obj = null;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 53066779,
            "question_id": 4449721
        }
    ],
